---
import TalleyPage from '../../../../components/talley-wealth/TalleyPage.astro';
import CtaSection from '../../../../components/talley-wealth/CtaSection.astro';

const primaryServices = [
  {
    title: 'Financial Planning',
    href: '/services/financial-planning',
    label: 'The full picture',
    body: 'For the questions that cannot be answered well by looking at one account, one tax return, or one projection.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Retirement Planning',
    href: '/services/retirement-planning',
    label: 'Work becomes optional',
    body: 'For families trying to understand when retirement is realistic, how income will work, and what could change the answer.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Tax Planning',
    href: '/services/tax-planning',
    label: 'Before the year is over',
    body: 'For business profit, Roth windows, capital gains, equity comp, retirement income, and other decisions that should not wait until filing season.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Investment Management',
    href: '/services/investment-management',
    label: 'Built around the plan',
    body: 'For portfolios that need to support retirement income, tax strategy, concentration risk, cash flow, and the life the money is meant to fund.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Business Owner Planning',
    href: '/services/business-owner-planning',
    label: 'Profit, taxes, and personal wealth',
    body: 'For owners who want a thinking partner around tax strategy, owner pay, retirement plans, business cash flow, and money outside the company.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The Keystone Method™',
    href: '/how-we-work/keystone-method',
    label: 'Where the work starts',
    body: 'The structured planning engagement where the scattered questions become a plan strong enough to guide what happens next.',
  },
];

const moments = [
  'Retirement is close enough that "someday" has turned into a real decision.',
  'The business is doing well, but the tax bill is starting to feel out of hand.',
  'You inherited money and want a careful, plain-English plan before making big moves.',
  'Equity compensation, benefits, or a concentrated position has made the tax and investment choices more complicated.',
  'You have accounts, a CPA, maybe an old plan, but still feel like no one is helping you think through the whole decision.',
];

const planningAreas = [
  'Retirement income',
  'Tax strategy',
  'Investment management',
  'Business-owner decisions',
  'Equity compensation',
  'Estate and beneficiary review',
  'Cash flow',
  'Insurance and risk',
  'Charitable giving',
];
---

<TalleyPage
  title="Services | Talley Wealth"
  description="Financial planning, tax planning, retirement planning, investment management, and business-owner planning from Talley Wealth in Johnson City, TN."
>
  <section class="bg-muted/35">
    <div class="section-container grid min-h-[620px] items-center gap-12 py-20 lg:grid-cols-[0.95fr_1fr]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Services</p>
        <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-4xl font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-primary md:text-5xl">
          Advice for the financial decisions that need more than a quick answer.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Most people do not reach out because they want a menu of services. They reach out because retirement is getting real, taxes are getting more visible, a business is changing, equity comp is vesting, or money decisions have started to feel too important to keep guessing on.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/get-started" class="inline-flex rounded-md bg-accent px-6 py-4 font-bold text-accent-foreground transition hover:bg-accent/90">Schedule an Explore Call</a>
          <a href="/how-we-work/keystone-method" class="inline-flex rounded-md border border-primary/20 bg-background px-6 py-4 font-bold text-primary transition hover:bg-card">See the planning process</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border/40 bg-card p-7 shadow-elegant-lg">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">When people usually reach out</p>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
          {moments.map((moment) => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
              <span>{moment}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="section-container py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">What we help with</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-primary md:text-4xl">
          The service matters less than the decision it supports.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          A retirement question can become a tax question. A tax question can become an investment question. A business question can become a family wealth question. The goal is to get the decision right, then make the right parts move.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {primaryServices.map((service) => (
          <a href={service.href} class="group flex h-full flex-col rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-elegant transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-elegant-lg">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-accent">{service.label}</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary transition group-hover:text-accent">{service.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 flex-1 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">{service.body}</p>
            <span class="mt-6 inline-flex text-sm font-bold text-accent">Read more <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;-&gt;</span></span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-card">
    <div class="section-container grid gap-12 py-20 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1fr]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Planning areas</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-primary md:text-4xl">
          The work is built around what your situation actually requires.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Keystone is usually where this starts. We lay out the relevant decisions, decide what belongs in the plan, reshape what needs work, and build a practical sequence of next steps.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {planningAreas.map((area) => (
          <div class="rounded-md border border-border bg-background p-4 text-sm font-semibold text-primary shadow-sm">{area}</div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
    <div class="section-container grid gap-10 py-20 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1fr]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Where to start</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold leading-tight md:text-4xl">Start with the question that is already on your mind.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-primary-foreground/78">
        <p>You do not need to know which service page fits before reaching out. If there is enough going on that you want a real advisor conversation, the Explore Call is the simple first step.</p>
        <p>If it looks like Keystone is the right next move, we will talk through that. If it is not a fit, David will say so directly.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="inline-flex rounded-md bg-accent px-6 py-3 font-bold text-accent-foreground transition hover:bg-accent/90">Schedule an Explore Call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaSection
    title="Want to see who this tends to fit?"
    description="The services page explains the work. The Who We Help page is the better place to see the situations where that work usually becomes valuable."
    primaryText="See Who We Help"
    primaryHref="/who-we-help"
    secondaryText="Review Pricing"
    secondaryHref="/pricing"
  />
</TalleyPage>
